@MACRO BOLD  "@{B} $1 @{UB}"
@MACRO SHINE "@{FG SHINE} $1 @{FG TEXT}"

@REM "@FONT Helvetica.font 14"

@INDEX "Index"

@NODE "Index" "Savvy Index:"

   @{BOLD "Savvy Index:"}
    
   @{" General Info      " LINK "Main"}

   @{" Menu Items        " LINK "MenuItems"} -- About, Help & Quit
    
   @{" Vanilla Keys      " LINK "VanillaKeys"} - Satanic KeyPresses

   @{" Author            " LINK "Author"} - Who wrote this great program?

   @{B}GADGETS:@{UB}
   @{" WorkGroups        " LINK "WGroups"} - The available Workgroups to use
   @{" WorkGroup Members " LINK "WGrpMembers"} - What each Workgroup contains

   @{" Add New Workgroup " LINK "AddWGrp"} - Creates new workgroups
   @{" Delete  Workgroup " LINK "DeleteWGrp"} - Deletes old workgroups

   @{" Run as Volume     " LINK "RunVolume"} - Mount fileshare as a Workbench Volume
   @{" Run as Device     " LINK "RunDevice"} - Mount fileshare as a device

   @{" Add New Member    " LINK "AddMember"} - Create a new workgroup member (fileshare)
   @{" Delete Member     " LINK "DeleteMember"} - Delete an old workgoup member

   @{" Edit ToolTypes    " LINK "EditTTButton"} - Edit/View the Savvy.info @{" ToolTypesĀ" LINK "ToolTypes"}
   @{" Activate Button   " LINK "ActivateButton"} - Try to mount a new fileshare
   @{" Exit Button       " LINK "ExitButton"} - Exit the Savvy program.

   @{" Activate with User%Password.. " LINK "ActivatePasswordButton"} - Try to mount a new fileshare
   @{" Disconnect Service..          " LINK "DisconnectButton"} - Try to Unmount a fileshare

   @{" Send Message to..             " LINK "SendMsgButton"} - Send a WinPopup message!

   @{" smbfs Documentation " LINK "smbfs.doc"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Main" "Savvy General Information:"
@PREV "Index"

   @{BOLD "Savvy General Information:"}

   A GUI for editing/viewing Samba file shares, then running them with smbfs.

   The main reason for this program is to use smbfs without having to remember all
   of those pseky command line arguments. @{FG SHINE}
   NOTE:  Savvy does not allow you to specify all of the command line arguments
          that smbfs knows about, just the more common ones.@{FG TEXT}

   NOTE:  The original @{" smbfs documentation " LINK "smbfs.doc"} describes how to stop a connection,
          Savvy cannot do this (yet!) through the GUI.

   You must read the @{" smbfs documentation " LINK "smbfs.doc"} in order to figure out what to place in the
   @{" WorkGroupsList " LINK "ToolTypes"} file & the WorkGroup file(s).
   The WorkGroupsList file should only contain a list of all the WorkGroup file(s)
   that you want Savvy to have access to.  For example, if your workgroupslist file is named
   SavvyGroupsList & only contains SavvyWorkGroup, then Savvy knows that it should
   read SavvyWorkGroup in order to find all of the shared resources available for @{" smbfs " LINK "smbfs.doc"}
   to connect to.  The filename contained in WorkGroupsList should be the name of the
   Workgroup you intend to connect to, since it will be used as an argument to the smbfs
   program.  Samples are located in the Savvy: directory & are known to the Savvy.info Icon
   in its ToolTypes.
   
   SEE ALSO, @{" ToolTypes " LINK "ToolTypes"}, @{" Index " LINK "Index"}

  @{BOLD HISTORY}
       1.7 Added the @{B}Send Message to..@{UB} Button to the GUI.
       
       1.6 Fixed the broken Edit Tooltypes Button as well as the broken Help
           menu item.  Also, added a Cancel Button to the String Requester.
	   The Help key (Scroll Lock) is also working now.
       
       1.5 Added the Activate with User%Password Button.
       
       1.4 Added the Disconnect Service Button.
       
       1.1 Re-compiled for the AmigaOne PPC & AmigaOS4.0
       
       1.0 Savvy is now working correctly!

@ENDNODE

@NODE "SendMsgButton" "Send a WinPopup message:"
@PREV "Main"
   Pressing this button will bring up a Requester for your message and which computer to send it to.
   The GUI is self-explanatory.  The Cursor Up and Down arrows move through the ListView Gadget items,
   and the @{" i " LINK "VanillaKeys"} and @{" h " LINK "VanillaKeys"} keys are also present.
      
  @{B}WARNINGS@{UB}      @{FG SHINE}
    The PC that you're sending the messasge to has to have WinPopup.exe in the C:\Windows directory.
    This is only true for versions of Windows 98SE & older! @{FG TEXT}
    For some reason, Microsoft removed it for Windows NT, and I know that it's @{B}NOT@{UB} present in
    WindowsXP Home Edition.    

@ENDNODE

@NODE "MenuItems" "PROJECT Menu Items:"
@PREV Main
@NEXT Index
   @{BOLD "PROJECT Menu Items:"}   

   Currently, there are only three menu items available to the User of Savvy:
   @{FG SHINE}
   PROJECT @{FG TEXT}
   1. About -- This item displays a brief informative message about the Savvy program.
   2. Help  -- This item should display this amigaguide file to you.  If it does not,
               then check the @{" HelpViewer " LINK "ToolTypes"} ToolType for a correct
	       program that displays amigaguide files & that you have Savvy.guide
	       (but then, you must have it or you wouldn't be reading this!)
   3. Quit  -- This item simply exits the Savvy program.

   See Also, @{" Vanilla Keys " LINK "VanillaKeys"}
   
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ToolTypes" "ToolTypes recognized by Savvy:"
@PREV "Main"

   @{B}ToolTypes used by Savvy:@{UB}
@{FG SHINE}
       ToolType:               Default Value:         NOTES:
       ~~~~~~~~~               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~         ~~~~~~ @{FG TEXT}
       ProgramDirectory      = Savvy:                 (Setup by the installation script)
       DefaultWorkGroup      = SavvyWorkGroup         (Change to your network WorkGroup)
       WorkGroupsList        = SavvyGroupsList        (Contains a line that names SavvyWorkGroup file)
       DefaultConnectionType = VOLUME [or DEVICE]     (See @{" smbfs Documentation " LINK "smbfs.doc"})
       SMBFSCommand          = SAMBA:Bin/smbfs        (Change to the location of smbfs)
       MsgCommand            = SAMBA:Bin/smbclient -M (Change to the location of smbfs)
       CacheSize             = 1000                   (See @{" smbfs Documentation " LINK "smbfs.doc"})
       DefaultUser           = PCGuest                (Normally, you should not change this)
       ToolsEditor           = ToolTypesEditor        (You can change this to an Icon editor that allows
                                                       you to edit ToolTypes as well).
       HelpViewer            = MultiView              (Something that can display amigaguide files)
      
@ENDNODE

@NODE "AddMember"
@PREV "Main"
@{FG SHINE}
   WARNING:  When adding a new item, be sure that an empty (blank) item is highlighted in the
             ListView Gadget first! @{FG TEXT}
		
   When you wish to add a new fileshare member to a Workgroup, you must first
   enter the name of the Server/fileshare into the String Gadget below the @{" WorkGroup Members " LINK "WGrpMembers"}
   ListView Gadget, then press & release this button.
   @{FG SHINE}
   NOTE:  Savvy will update the current WorkGroup file to reflect what you do with this button.
          This is why there are no Load/Save menu items with this program, it's done automatically.@{FG TEXT}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "DeleteMember"
@PREV "AddMember"

   When you wish to delete a fileshare member from a Workgroup, you must first
   select/highlight the undesired member in the @{" Workgroup Members " LINK "WGrpMembers"} ListView Gadget, 
   then press & release this button.

   @{FG SHINE}
   NOTE:  Savvy will update the current WorkGroup file to reflect what you do with this button.
          This is why there are no Load/Save menu items with this program, it's done automatically.@{FG TEXT}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "WGroups" "WorkGroups ListView Gadget:"
@PREV "Main"

   This part of the GUI displays all of the WorkGroups that are found in the 
   @{" WorkGroupsList ToolType " LINK "ToolTypes"}, located in the Icon.  When you highlight a Workgroup name,
   Savvy will update the @{" Workgroup Members " LINK "WGrpMembers"} ListView & copy the highlighted item into
   the String Gadget below this ListView Gadget.  Unless you have a complex network, this
   ListView Gadget will usually only have one entry in it.  This entry is the name of the
   WorkGroup that your network is known by.  

   (See also, @{" smbfs docs " LINK "smbfs.doc"})
@ENDNODE

@NODE "WGrpMembers" "Workgroup Members ListView Gadget:"
@PREV "Main"

   This part of the GUI displays all of the different Computers & their fileshares that are
   found in the currently selected @{" WorkGroup " LINK "WGroups"}.
   When you highlight a Workgroup Member name, Savvy will copy the highlighted item into
   the String Gadget below this ListView Gadget.  The @{" documentation " LINK "smbfs.doc"} for smbfs will explain
   what each line in this ListView should contain & where/how to find the correct information
   to enter into this Gadget.

   (See also, @{" smbfs docs " LINK "smbfs.doc"})
@ENDNODE

@NODE "AddWGrp" "Add New Workgroup BUtton:"

@{FG SHINE}
   WARNING:  When adding a new item, be sure that an empty (blank) item is highlighted in the
             ListView Gadget first! @{FG TEXT}

   When you wish to add a new Workgroup, you must first enter the name of the Workgroup
   into the String Gadget below the @{" WorkGroups " LINK "WGroups"}
   ListView Gadget, then press & release this button.

   @{FG SHINE}
   NOTE:  Savvy will update the current WorkGroup file to reflect what you do with this button.
          This is why there are no Load/Save menu items with this program, it's done automatically.@{FG TEXT}

   (See also, @{" smbfs docs " LINK "smbfs.doc"})
@ENDNODE

@NODE "DeleteWGrp" "Delete  Workgroup Button:"

   When you wish to delete a Workgroup, you must first enter the name of the Workgroup
   into the String Gadget below the @{" WorkGroups " LINK "WGroups"}
   ListView Gadget, then press & release this button.

   @{FG SHINE}
   NOTE:  Savvy will update the current WorkGroup file to reflect what you do with this button.
          This is why there are no Load/Save menu items with this program, it's done automatically.@{FG TEXT}
@ENDNODE

@NODE "RunVolume" "Run as Volume Button:"

   When this Gadget is checked, Savvy will know to mount the next @{" Activated " LINK "ActivateButton"} fileshare as a Volume.
   This differs from @{" Run as Device " LINK "RunDevice"} in that a Volume will be displayed as a disk Icon on 
   Workbench.   
@ENDNODE

@NODE "RunDevice" "Run as Device Button:"

   When this Gadget is checked, Savvy will know to mount the next @{" Activated " LINK "ActivateButton"} fileshare as a Device.
   This differs from @{" Run as Volume " LINK "RunVolume"} in that a Device will NOT be displayed as a disk Icon on 
   Workbench.   
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ExitButton" "ExitButton Button:"
@PREV "Main"

   Pressing & releasing this button will exit the Savvy program.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "EditTTButton" "EditTTButton Button:"
@PREV "Main"

   Pressing & releasing this button will display the ToolTypes editor that is 
   specified with the @{" ToolsEditor " LINK "ToolTypes"} ToolType in the Savvy.info Icon.  You can view/edit the @{" ToolTypes " LINK "ToolTypes"}
   for the Savvy program with it.   The default @{" ToolTypesEditor " LINK "ToolTypesEditor.guide/Main"} program is supplied with Savvy.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "ActivateButton" "ActivateButton Button:"
@PREV "Main"

   Pressing & releasing this button will bring up a String Requester for you to fill in.
   Fill it with the name of the @{" Volume " LINK "RunVolume"} or @{" device " LINK "RunDevice"} you want your Amiga to mount the fileshare as.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "VanillaKeys" "Keys that Savvy recognizes:"
@PREV "Main"
  @{SHINE "a or A:"}Same as pressing the @{" Add New Workgroup " LINK "AddWGrp"} Button.
    
  @{SHINE "n or N:"}Same as pressing the @{" Add New Member    " LINK "AddMember"} Button.
    
  @{SHINE "e or E:"}Same as pressing the @{" Edit ToolTypes    " LINK "EditTTButton"} Button.

  @{SHINE "t or T:"}Same as pressing the @{" ACTIVATE!         " LINK "ActivateButton"} Button.

  @{SHINE "x or X:"}Same as pressing the @{" EXIT!             " LINK "ExitButton"} Button.

  @{SHINE "s or S:"}Same as pressing the @{" Send Message to.. " LINK "SendMsgButton"} Button.

  PROJECT MenuItems:
  @{SHINE "i or I:"}Shows an Information requester.
  @{SHINE "h or H:"}Display the Savvy.guide file (which you are now reading!)
          The Help key (Scroll Lock) & the @{B}?@{UB} also do this!
	      
  @{SHINE "q or Q:"}Alternative exit point for the Savvy program.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "ActivatePasswordButton" "Activate with User%Password.."

   This button operates like the @{" ACTIVATE " LINK "ActivateButton"} button, with the exception of asking
   you for a User name & Password known to the remote computer (& to you!) that you're trying
   to connect to.  This is only necessary for fileshares that are password-protected.  
   All other fileshares should connect using the @{" ACTIVATE " LINK "ActivateButton"} button.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "DisconnectButton" "Disconnect Service.. BUtton:"

   This Button will try to Unmount a fileshare by running the following command:
   @{FG SHINE}   
      Break NAME "@{B}smbfs //netBIOSName/FileShare@{UB}" @{FG TEXT}

   where //netBIOSName/FileShare is the currently selected member of the 
   @{"ĀWorkgroups Members: " LINK "WGrpMembers"} ListView Gadget.
   
   If the command is successful, the FileShare Icon (for @{" VOLUME-type " LINK "RunVolume"} connections)
   will disappear from the Workbench.
   
@ENDNODE

